  • Possession of Methamphetamine, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).
  • Possession of THC (2nd+ Offense), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.  (If felony) Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea. Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  DA confirms compliance with victim witness rights.  Statement by Bob Dore.  Sentencing statement by DA.  Sentencing statement by Atty Zamzow.  Statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

COUNT 1 - SWD, and places the defendant on probation for 3 years.

-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample.

-120 days county jail, with huber to commence immediately.  Court grants out of county service and out of county travel.  Court grants the defendant 81 days of sentence credit.
-Court costs.  Court grants the defendant 60 days to pay or payment plan.
-DNA Sample.
